    slug: "khareed-o-farokht-kay-masail",
    description: `Khareed o Farokht Kay Masail is a comprehensive Urdu-language book that addresses the Islamic rulings and guidelines related to buying, selling, and all forms of commercial transactions. In an era of increasingly complex economic activities, this book serves as an essential reference for Muslims who want to ensure that their business dealings, purchases, and sales conform to the principles of Islamic law (fiqh al-mu'amalat). The book systematically covers the major categories of trade-related issues, drawing upon the Quran, the authentic hadith of Prophet Muhammad (peace be upon him), and the established rulings of the major schools of Islamic jurisprudence to provide clear, evidence-based guidance on every aspect of commercial transactions. The author begins by establishing the foundational principles of Islamic commerce, including the importance of mutual consent in transactions, the prohibition of riba (interest and usury), the requirement of honesty and transparency in describing goods, and the general principle that all transactions are permissible unless specifically prohibited by Islamic law. The book then addresses specific types of transactions in detail, covering topics such as cash sales (bay al-naqd), credit sales (bay al-nasiyah), advance payment purchases (bay al-salam), manufacturing orders (bay al-istisna), and pawn transactions (al-rahin). Each type of transaction is explained with its conditions, requirements, and the specific rulings that govern its validity according to Islamic law. The book also covers common issues that arise in modern buying and selling, including online shopping, instalment plans, credit card transactions, insurance, and various forms of modern financial products, evaluating each against the criteria of Islamic permissibility. Specific chapters address the ruling on defective goods (ayb), the right of inspection before purchase (khiyar al-ru'yah), the right of return (khiyar al-'ayb), the prohibition of fraud and deception (gharar), and the rules surrounding price manipulation, hoarding (ihtikar), and artificial price inflation. The author provides practical guidance on how to conduct business in a manner that is both Islamically compliant and commercially viable, addressing the concerns of both buyers and sellers. The language of the book is clear and accessible Urdu that makes complex legal discussions understandable to readers who may not have formal training in Islamic jurisprudence. Khareed o Farokht Kay Masail is an invaluable resource for business owners, shopkeepers, traders, consumers, students of Islamic law, and anyone who participates in commercial activities and wishes to ensure that their dealings are in accordance with Islamic teachings.`,
    metaDescription: "Khareed o Farokht Kay Masail is a comprehensive Urdu guide to Islamic rulings on buying, selling, and commercial transactions with practical fiqh guidance."
