    slug: "khawateen-aur-ramadan-ul-mubarak-1",
    description: `Khawateen Aur Ramadan ul Mubarak (duplicate listing) is an Urdu-language Islamic book that serves as a focused and practical guide for Muslim women seeking to make the most of the holy month of Ramadan. This edition addresses the full spectrum of concerns that Muslim women encounter during Ramadan, combining scholarly fiqh-based guidance with motivational and practical advice that helps women observe the month in a manner that is both religiously correct and personally manageable. The book recognises that Muslim women often bear significant domestic and caregiving responsibilities during Ramadan, including preparing sehri (pre-dawn meals) and iftar (fast-breaking meals) for their families, managing household routines during extended fasting hours, and caring for children and elderly family members. Rather than treating these responsibilities as obstacles to worship, the book presents them as opportunities for earning reward and draws upon hadith narrations that highlight the immense spiritual merit of serving fasting family members. The fiqh section provides detailed rulings on the specific issues that most commonly affect women during Ramadan. These include the ruling on fasting during menstruation and postpartum bleeding, with clear explanations of when fasting is obligatory, when it is permitted, and when it is prohibited; the method for making up missed fasts and the time frame within which they should be completed; the permissibility and conditions of fasting during pregnancy and breastfeeding, including the scholarly opinions on when a pregnant or nursing woman may break her fast and the requirement to make up those days; and the use of medication or other means to delay or regulate menstruation during Ramadan. The book also covers the proper method of performing Taraweeh prayers at home, the recommended supplications and dhikr for Ramadan, the etiquette of reciting the Quran, and the special acts of worship associated with the last ten nights of Ramadan. The author provides practical tips for managing time and energy during Ramadan, including suggestions for meal planning, delegating household tasks, and creating a personal worship schedule that is realistic and sustainable. The tone of the book is supportive and encouraging, acknowledging the challenges that women face while emphasising the vast spiritual rewards that await those who observe Ramadan with sincerity and dedication. Written in clear and accessible Urdu, this book is an essential companion for Muslim women during the blessed month and a valuable reference that they can return to year after year.`,
