    slug: "khawateen-k-liye-hadith-ki-kitaab",
    description: `Khawateen K Liye Hadith Ki Kitaab is an Urdu-language compilation of authentic hadith narrations from Prophet Muhammad (peace be upon him) that has been specifically selected and organised for a female readership. Recognising that the hadith literature contains a vast number of narrations that address women's issues, family life, domestic matters, and the specific spiritual concerns of Muslim women, this book curates a focused collection that makes the Prophetic guidance most relevant to women readily accessible in a single volume. The compiler has drawn upon the most authoritative sources of hadith, including Sahih al-Bukhari, Sahih Muslim, Sunan Abu Dawud, Sunan at-Tirmidhi, Sunan an-Nasa'i, and Sunan Ibn Majah, ensuring that every narration included in the book meets the highest standards of authenticity. The hadith are organised into thematic chapters that correspond to the major areas of a Muslim woman's life and religious practice. Chapters cover topics including the virtues and rights of women in Islam, the importance of modesty and hijab, the rulings related to prayer, fasting, and pilgrimage as they specifically apply to women, the guidance on marriage, marital relations, and the rights and responsibilities of spouses, the instructions on child-rearing and family management, the encouragement for seeking knowledge, the etiquettes of social interaction, and the descriptions of the righteous women of the early Muslim community who serve as role models. Each hadith is presented in its original Arabic text alongside a clear Urdu translation, and brief explanatory notes are provided where needed to clarify the context or meaning of the narration. The book also includes the biographical details of the many female narrators of hadith, highlighting the important role that women played in preserving and transmitting the Prophetic tradition. This aspect of the book serves to inspire Muslim women by demonstrating that women have been active participants in Islamic scholarship since the earliest days of the faith. The compiler has taken care to select hadith that address contemporary concerns while remaining firmly grounded in the classical sources, making the book relevant to the lives of modern Muslim women without compromising on authenticity. The language is clear and accessible Urdu that makes the content understandable to readers of varying educational backgrounds. Khawateen K Liye Hadith Ki Kitaab serves as both a daily reference for practical religious guidance and an inspirational work that encourages Muslim women to deepen their connection with the Prophetic tradition.`,
