    slug: "khawateen-kai-lye-80-ihkam-e-quran",
    description: `Khawateen Kai Lye 80 Ihkam e Quran is a specialised Urdu-language book that presents eighty essential rulings, teachings, and commandments derived from the Quran that are particularly relevant to the lives of Muslim women. The title indicates that this book has been specifically compiled and written with a female readership in mind, selecting Quranic injunctions and guidance that address the unique roles, responsibilities, challenges, and spiritual needs of women in Islam. The book bridges the gap between the general study of the Quran and the practical application of its teachings to the everyday lives of Muslim women, making the divine guidance accessible, organised, and directly relevant. Each of the eighty selected rulings (ahkam) is presented with the relevant Quranic verse or verses in Arabic, followed by a clear Urdu translation and a detailed explanation that contextualises the ruling and explains its practical implications. The rulings are drawn from across the Quran, covering a broad spectrum of topics that affect women's lives. These include the spiritual obligations common to all Muslims such as prayer, fasting, charity, and pilgrimage, with specific attention to how these obligations apply to women in their particular circumstances; the Quranic guidance on modesty, hijab, and the Islamic dress code; the injunctions related to marriage, family life, and the rights and responsibilities of spouses; the rulings concerning inheritance, property rights, and financial independence for women; the commands related to the upbringing and education of children; the guidance on social interaction, speech, and conduct; and the spiritual virtues that all Muslims, and women in particular, are encouraged to cultivate such as patience, gratitude, modesty, and humility. The book also addresses Quranic verses that are sometimes misunderstood or misinterpreted regarding women's status and rights in Islam, providing accurate explanations that are grounded in the classical tafsir (exegesis) tradition and the consensus of the scholars. The commentary accompanying each ruling draws upon the major works of tafsir, including the works of Ibn Kathir, at-Tabari, and al-Qurtubi, ensuring that the explanations are both authentic and well-sourced. The organisational structure of the book, grouping the eighty rulings into logical categories, makes it easy for readers to find guidance on specific topics and to use the book as a reference for日常 religious questions. Written in clear and accessible Urdu, this book is an essential addition to every Muslim woman's personal library, serving as both a comprehensive guide to Quranic teachings and an inspirational work that strengthens faith and encourages righteous conduct.`,
